oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Blount Mansion dining room
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Interior view of the dining room in the Blount Mansion. Original pine flooring and walls, mantel and doors, handmade, and side cupboards.
Blount mansion was the home of Governor of the Southwest Territory, William Blount. It served as the Capitol of the Southwest Territory.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Jim Thompson Co.
